PixelsPerSubdivisionX: Size of a single subdivision (in pixels) in X (for Diced mode)
PixelsPerSubdivisionY: Size of a single subdivision (in pixels) in Y (for Diced mode)
bAvoidVertexMerging: Experimental: Hint to the triangulation routine that extra vertices should be preserved
AlphaThreshold: Alpha threshold for a transparent pixel (range 0..1, anything equal or below this value will be considered unimportant)
DetailAmount: Amount to detail to consider when shrink-wrapping (range 0..1, 0 = low detail, 1 = high detail)
SimplifyEpsilon: This is the threshold below which multiple vertices will be merged together when doing shrink-wrapping.  Higher values result in fewer vertices.
